*Highlighted section: Constructor and Initialization*

The constructor initializes the student's full name, unique ID, and GPA. It ensures that all data members are properly assigned and validates that the GPA is within a reasonable academic range (0.0 to 4.0).

```cpp
UndergraduateStudentProfile::UndergraduateStudentProfile(const std::string& name, const std::string& id, double gpa)
    : fullName(name), studentID(id), gpa(gpa) {
    if (gpa < 0.0 || gpa > 4.0) {
        gpa = 0.0; // Default to 0.0 if invalid
    }
}
```

